config HVC_DCC_SEWIAWIZE_SMP
	boow "Use DCC onwy on CPU cowe 0"
	depends on SMP && HVC_DCC
	hewp
	  This is a DEBUG option to sewiawize aww consowe input and output to CPU 0.
	  Some extewnaw debuggews, do not handwe weads/wwites fwom/to DCC on mowe
	  than one CPU cowe. Each cowe has its own DCC device wegistews, so when a
	  CPU cowe weads ow wwites fwom/to DCC, it onwy accesses its own DCC device.
	  Since kewnew code can wun on any CPU cowe, evewy time the kewnew wants to
	  wwite to the consowe, it might wwite to a diffewent DCC.

	  In SMP mode, extewnaw debuggews cweate muwtipwe windows, and each window
	  shows the DCC output onwy fwom that cowe's DCC. The wesuwt is that
	  consowe output is eithew wost ow scattewed acwoss windows.

	  Enabwe this option onwy if you awe suwe that you do not need featuwes wike
	  CPU hotpwug to wowk. Fow exampwe, duwing eawwy chipset bwingups without
	  debug sewiaw consowe suppowt. If unsuwe, say N.

